title: Live blog: The Phantom on Steele Sidebottom Gary Ablett and all things SuperCoach | The
text:
ROUND 14 SCORE: 2112
OVERALL RANKING: 12
AFTER letting Daniel Hannebery slide by last Thursday night, with the intention of trading in David Mundy for Rory Sloane, The Phantom eventually decided to take the slightly riskier path and bring in Magpie Steele Sidebottom.
If the skilful midfielder can start to go big, as we all know he can, Sidebottom could be a very important point of difference in the run home.
He was prolific in the first half last Friday before slowing slightly to finish with 107 SuperCoach points.
Read more below the blog module.
SuperCoach with The Phantom (Frame content direct link: http://embed.scribblelive.com/Embed/v7.aspx?Id=1368091 .)
While not hitting the heights of Hannebery’s 142 and Mundy’s 122, coming off three scores below 85, the signs were encouraging.
The extra cash will be used to bring in Gary Ablett in the next few weeks.
Speaking of the little master, who inspired the Suns to their second win of the season with 31 possessions, three goals and 124 points on his return, how are you planning to bring him in to your side?
Join The Phantom back here at 12.30PM to talk Ablett and all things SuperCoach.
